
Notes

See original !HELP

Register usage

R9  OP
R10 TOS - top of stack
R11 IP  - forth instruction pointer
R12 RP  - return pointer (return stack)
R13 SP  - data stack
R14 link - used by branch instructions
R15 PC	- program counter


Minor changes

modifications to work on the RISC PC.
Added code sync to allow the compiler to work on the StrongARM processor.

Other modifications
Changed the definition of centre: ( the window was not on the screen.)
Stopped processing the command line as it picks up garbage from the RISCOS buffer most of the time.

Updated current-dir$ to use the current file system 
 

FWIMP is the Wimp app that is run.
FCONS is a console app.

rebuild

.. The kernal

start FWIMP or FCONS
fload meta
kernal app is made (around 26k)
bye

.. The forth

click on kernal
fload extend
.. FWIMP is saved (around 140k)
bye
     
.. remake console app

clock on kernal
fload makeconsole
..FCONS is saved
bye


You now have a new forth

